# SYSTEM 3: NOTIFICATION DELIVERY SLA & RETRY CASCADE SPECIFICATION
## UNJYNX Multi-Channel Notification Orchestration Engine

### 3.1 ARCHITECTURE OVERVIEW

Inspired by Novu's workflow orchestration and Courier's automated failover, but custom-built for cost optimization (India market) and UNJYNX-specific needs.

Components:
1. Notification Orchestrator (Hono service) - Receives notification requests, resolves user preferences, creates jobs
2. BullMQ Queues (per channel) - Separate queue per channel for independent scaling
3. Channel Workers (per channel) - Process jobs, call provider APIs, track delivery
4. Fallback Cascade Engine - Moves failed notifications to next channel in cascade
5. Delivery Tracker - Records every state transition, calculates SLAs
6. Cost Controller - Enforces per-user per-channel spending limits
7. Dead Letter Queue - Captures permanently failed notifications for investigation

Flow:
```
Trigger (API/Scheduler/RRULE engine)
  -> Orchestrator (resolve user, preferences, cascade order)
    -> Primary Channel Queue (e.g., WhatsApp)
      -> Channel Worker (call Gupshup API)
        -> SUCCESS: Record delivery, done
        -> FAILURE: Retry with exponential backoff
          -> MAX_RETRIES: Fallback Cascade Engine
            -> Next Channel Queue (e.g., Telegram)
              -> ... (repeat)
                -> ALL CHANNELS EXHAUSTED: Dead Letter Queue + Alert
```

### 3.2 DELIVERY SLA PER CHANNEL

| Channel   | Provider (India)     | Delivery SLA | Latency SLA (p95) | Max Retries | Retry Window | Cost/msg (INR) |
|-----------|---------------------|-------------|-------------------|-------------|-------------|----------------|
| Push      | FCM                 | 85% (best effort) | <5s          | 2           | 5 min        | 0 (free)       |
| Telegram  | Bot API             | 99%+        | <3s               | 5           | 30 min       | 0 (free)       |
| WhatsApp  | Gupshup BSP         | 98%+        | <5s               | 3           | 15 min       | ~0.50          |
| Email     | SendGrid (prod) / Mailpit (dev) | 97%+ | <30s         | 5           | 2 hours      | ~0.07          |
| SMS       | MSG91 / Kaleyra     | 99%+        | <10s              | 3           | 15 min       | 0.15-0.25      |
| In-App    | WebSocket + Inbox   | 100% (store)| <1s (if online)   | 0           | -            | 0 (free)       |

Notes:
- Push delivery is "best effort" because FCM does not guarantee delivery (device offline, battery saver, etc.)
- In-App is always stored in database; real-time delivery via WebSocket is bonus
- WhatsApp template messages have a 24h delivery window from Meta
- SMS DND (Do Not Disturb) registry in India filters 10-15% of marketing messages

### 3.3 RETRY STRATEGY

PER-CHANNEL BULLMQ CONFIGURATION:

```typescript
// Queue definitions
const QUEUE_CONFIG = {
  'notification:push': {
    attempts: 3,
    backoff: { type: 'exponential', delay: 5000 },     // 5s, 10s, 20s
    timeout: 30_000,        // 30 second job timeout
    removeOnComplete: { age: 86400, count: 10000 },     // Keep 24h or 10K
    removeOnFail: false,    // Keep for DLQ analysis
  },
  'notification:telegram': {
    attempts: 5,
    backoff: { type: 'exponential', delay: 3000 },      // 3s, 6s, 12s, 24s, 48s
    timeout: 15_000,
    removeOnComplete: { age: 86400, count: 10000 },
    removeOnFail: false,
  },
  'notification:whatsapp': {
    attempts: 3,
    backoff: { type: 'exponential', delay: 10000 },     // 10s, 20s, 40s
    timeout: 30_000,
    removeOnComplete: { age: 86400, count: 10000 },
    removeOnFail: false,
  },
  'notification:email': {
    attempts: 5,
    backoff: { type: 'exponential', delay: 30000 },     // 30s, 60s, 120s, 240s, 480s
    timeout: 60_000,
    removeOnComplete: { age: 86400, count: 10000 },
    removeOnFail: false,
  },
  'notification:sms': {
    attempts: 3,
    backoff: { type: 'exponential', delay: 10000 },     // 10s, 20s, 40s
    timeout: 30_000,
    removeOnComplete: { age: 86400, count: 10000 },
    removeOnFail: false,
  },
} as const;
```

CUSTOM BACKOFF WITH ERROR-AWARE LOGIC:

```typescript
// Custom backoff strategy that considers error type
const notificationBackoff = (attemptsMade: number, type: string, err: Error, job: Job) => {
  const errorType = classifyError(err);
  
  switch (errorType) {
    case 'RATE_LIMITED':
      // Respect rate limit reset time from provider response
      const retryAfter = extractRetryAfter(err);
      return retryAfter ? retryAfter * 1000 : Math.pow(2, attemptsMade) * 30000;
    
    case 'INVALID_TOKEN':
    case 'USER_BLOCKED':
    case 'TEMPLATE_REJECTED':
      // Non-retryable: fail immediately, trigger cascade
      return -1;
    
    case 'PROVIDER_DOWN':
      // Longer backoff for provider outages
      return Math.min(Math.pow(2, attemptsMade) * 60000, 600000); // Max 10 min
    
    case 'NETWORK_ERROR':
    case 'TIMEOUT':
      // Standard exponential backoff
      return Math.pow(2, attemptsMade) * 5000;
    
    default:
      return Math.pow(2, attemptsMade) * 10000;
  }
};
```

ERROR CLASSIFICATION:

```typescript
type NotificationErrorType =
  | 'RATE_LIMITED'        // 429 from provider
  | 'INVALID_TOKEN'       // User's channel token expired/invalid
  | 'USER_BLOCKED'        // User blocked bot/number
  | 'TEMPLATE_REJECTED'   // WhatsApp template not approved
  | 'PROVIDER_DOWN'       // 5xx from provider
  | 'NETWORK_ERROR'       // DNS/TCP/TLS failure
  | 'TIMEOUT'             // Provider didn't respond in time
  | 'QUOTA_EXCEEDED'      // Monthly/daily quota hit
  | 'INVALID_CONTENT'     // Message content validation failed
  | 'DND_FILTERED'        // SMS DND registry block (India)
  | 'UNKNOWN';            // Unexpected error

const classifyError = (err: Error): NotificationErrorType => {
  if (err instanceof ProviderError) {
    if (err.statusCode === 429) return 'RATE_LIMITED';
    if (err.statusCode === 401 || err.statusCode === 403) return 'INVALID_TOKEN';
    if (err.statusCode >= 500) return 'PROVIDER_DOWN';
    if (err.code === 'TEMPLATE_NOT_APPROVED') return 'TEMPLATE_REJECTED';
    if (err.code === 'USER_BLOCKED_BOT') return 'USER_BLOCKED';
    if (err.code === 'DND_FILTERED') return 'DND_FILTERED';
  }
  if (err.code === 'ECONNREFUSED' || err.code === 'ENOTFOUND') return 'NETWORK_ERROR';
  if (err.code === 'ETIMEDOUT' || err.message.includes('timeout')) return 'TIMEOUT';
  return 'UNKNOWN';
};
```

NON-RETRYABLE ERROR HANDLING:
When classifyError returns a non-retryable type (INVALID_TOKEN, USER_BLOCKED, TEMPLATE_REJECTED, INVALID_CONTENT), the worker immediately skips retries and triggers the fallback cascade to the next channel. It also records the failure reason for the user's channel health status (auto-disable channels with persistent failures).

### 3.4 FALLBACK CASCADE

DEFAULT CASCADE ORDER (configurable per user):
1. Push (free, best effort, always attempted first)
2. Telegram (free, high delivery rate)
3. WhatsApp (paid, highest engagement)
4. Email (near-free, reliable)
5. SMS (paid, last resort, highest urgency)

USER CONFIGURABLE CASCADE:
Users can reorder their cascade in app settings. Example:
- User A (cost-conscious): Push -> Telegram -> Email (never SMS/WhatsApp)
- User B (urgency-focused): WhatsApp -> SMS -> Push -> Telegram -> Email
- User C (minimal): Push only

CASCADE ENGINE LOGIC:

```typescript
interface CascadeConfig {
  userId: string;
  channels: CascadeChannel[];
}

interface CascadeChannel {
  channel: NotificationChannel;
  enabled: boolean;
  priority: number;           // Lower = tried first
  maxDailyMessages: number;   // Per-user per-channel limit
  quietHoursStart?: string;   // "22:00" in user's timezone
  quietHoursEnd?: string;     // "07:00" in user's timezone
  costLimitDaily?: number;    // In INR, for paid channels
}

type NotificationChannel = 'push' | 'telegram' | 'whatsapp' | 'email' | 'sms' | 'in_app';

const executeCascade = async (
  notificationId: string,
  userId: string,
  failedChannel: NotificationChannel,
  errorType: NotificationErrorType,
) => {
  const cascade = await getUserCascade(userId);
  const failedPriority = cascade.channels.find(c => c.channel === failedChannel)?.priority ?? 999;
  
  // Find next enabled channel with higher priority number
  const nextChannels = cascade.channels
    .filter(c => c.enabled && c.priority > failedPriority)
    .sort((a, b) => a.priority - b.priority);
  
  if (nextChannels.length === 0) {
    // All channels exhausted -> Dead Letter Queue
    await moveToDeadLetterQueue(notificationId, userId, 'all_channels_exhausted');
    await incrementMetric('notification_cascade_exhausted_total');
    return;
  }
  
  const nextChannel = nextChannels[0];
  
  // Check rate limits and quiet hours before dispatching
  if (isInQuietHours(nextChannel, userId)) {
    // Delay until quiet hours end
    const delayMs = calculateDelayUntilQuietHoursEnd(nextChannel, userId);
    await addToChannelQueue(nextChannel.channel, notificationId, { delay: delayMs });
    return;
  }
  
  if (await isDailyLimitReached(userId, nextChannel.channel, nextChannel.maxDailyMessages)) {
    // Skip this channel, try next
    await executeCascade(notificationId, userId, nextChannel.channel, 'QUOTA_EXCEEDED');
    return;
  }
  
  // Dispatch to next channel
  await addToChannelQueue(nextChannel.channel, notificationId, {});
  await recordCascadeStep(notificationId, failedChannel, nextChannel.channel, errorType);
};
```

### 3.5 RATE LIMITING

PER-USER PER-CHANNEL DAILY LIMITS (defaults, user can lower but not raise above plan max):

| Channel   | Free Plan Max/Day | Pro Plan Max/Day | Cost Protection |
|-----------|------------------|------------------|-----------------|
| Push      | 20               | 50               | N/A (free)      |
| Telegram  | 30               | 100              | N/A (free)      |
| WhatsApp  | 5                | 20               | INR 10/day max  |
| Email     | 10               | 30               | $0.03/day max   |
| SMS       | 3                | 10               | INR 2.50/day max|
| In-App    | Unlimited        | Unlimited        | N/A             |

SYSTEM-WIDE RATE LIMITS:

| Channel   | Global TPS (Transactions/Second) | Provider Limit                        |
|-----------|----------------------------------|---------------------------------------|
| Push      | 500 TPS                          | FCM: 500 TPS per project             |
| Telegram  | 30 TPS (per bot)                 | Telegram: 30 msg/s to different chats |
| WhatsApp  | 80 TPS (BSP tier)                | Gupshup: 80 TPS (scale tier)         |
| Email     | 100 TPS                          | SendGrid: 100/s (Pro plan)           |
| SMS       | 50 TPS                           | MSG91: 50 TPS default                |

IMPLEMENTATION (Redis-based sliding window):

```typescript
const checkRateLimit = async (
  userId: string,
  channel: NotificationChannel,
  maxPerDay: number,
): Promise<{ allowed: boolean; remaining: number; resetAt: Date }> => {
  const key = `ratelimit:${channel}:${userId}:${getTodayKey(userId)}`;
  
  const current = await redis.incr(key);
  if (current === 1) {
    // First message today, set expiry to end of user's day
    await redis.expireat(key, getEndOfDayTimestamp(userId));
  }
  
  if (current > maxPerDay) {
    await redis.decr(key); // Undo the increment
    return {
      allowed: false,
      remaining: 0,
      resetAt: getEndOfDay(userId),
    };
  }
  
  return {
    allowed: true,
    remaining: maxPerDay - current,
    resetAt: getEndOfDay(userId),
  };
};

// System-wide TPS limiter using token bucket
const checkSystemRateLimit = async (channel: NotificationChannel): Promise<boolean> => {
  const key = `ratelimit:system:${channel}`;
  const maxTps = SYSTEM_TPS_LIMITS[channel];
  
  // Sliding window counter (1-second window)
  const now = Date.now();
  const windowStart = now - 1000;
  
  // Use Redis sorted set for precise sliding window
  await redis.zremrangebyscore(key, 0, windowStart);
  const count = await redis.zcard(key);
  
  if (count >= maxTps) {
    return false; // Throttle
  }
  
  await redis.zadd(key, now, `${now}:${Math.random()}`);
  await redis.expire(key, 2); // Auto-cleanup
  return true;
};
```

### 3.6 DELIVERY TRACKING

MESSAGE STATUS STATE MACHINE:

```
CREATED -> QUEUED -> PROCESSING -> SENT -> DELIVERED -> READ -> ACTED
                        |                      |
                        v                      v
                    RETRYING              (terminal)
                        |
                        v
                    FAILED -> CASCADING -> (next channel starts at QUEUED)
                        |
                        v
                    DEAD_LETTER
```

DELIVERY STATUS ENUM AND SCHEMA:

```typescript
export const notificationStatusEnum = pgEnum('notification_status', [
  'created',       // Notification request received
  'queued',        // Added to BullMQ queue
  'processing',    // Worker picked up the job
  'sent',          // Provider accepted the message
  'delivered',     // Provider confirmed delivery (webhook/callback)
  'read',          // User opened/read the message (webhook/callback)
  'acted',         // User took action (mark done, snooze, etc.)
  'retrying',      // Failed, waiting for retry
  'failed',        // All retries exhausted for this channel
  'cascading',     // Moving to fallback channel
  'dead_letter',   // All channels exhausted, permanently failed
]);

export const notificationChannelEnum = pgEnum('notification_channel', [
  'push', 'telegram', 'whatsapp', 'email', 'sms', 'in_app',
]);

export const notificationTypeEnum = pgEnum('notification_type', [
  'task_reminder',      // Due date reminder
  'recurring_reminder', // Recurring task reminder
  'daily_content',      // Daily quote/content delivery
  'system',             // Account alerts, plan changes, etc.
  'social',             // Friend activity, team updates
  'escalation',         // Overdue task escalation
]);
```

DRIZZLE SCHEMA - NOTIFICATIONS TABLE:

```typescript
export const notifications = pgTable('notifications', {
  id: uuid('id').primaryKey().defaultRandom(),
  userId: uuid('user_id').references(() => profiles.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' }).notNull(),
  taskId: uuid('task_id').references(() => tasks.id, { onDelete: 'set null' }),
  type: notificationTypeEnum('type').notNull(),
  
  // Content
  title: text('title').notNull(),
  body: text('body').notNull(),
  actionUrl: text('action_url'),              // Deep link for app navigation
  contentId: uuid('content_id'),              // For daily_content type
  
  // Scheduling
  scheduledAt: timestamp('scheduled_at', { withTimezone: true }).notNull(),
  expiresAt: timestamp('expires_at', { withTimezone: true }),  // After this, don't bother sending
  
  // Priority (affects queue priority)
  priority: integer('priority').default(5).notNull(),  // 1=highest, 10=lowest
  
  // Cascade tracking
  cascadeId: uuid('cascade_id'),              // Groups all attempts across channels
  cascadeOrder: integer('cascade_order').default(0).notNull(),  // 0=first attempt
  
  // Metadata
  metadata: jsonb('metadata'),                // Channel-specific data, template vars
  
  createdAt: timestamp('created_at', { withTimezone: true }).defaultNow().notNull(),
  updatedAt: timestamp('updated_at', { withTimezone: true }).defaultNow().notNull(),
}, (table) => [
  index('notifications_user_id_idx').on(table.userId),
  index('notifications_task_id_idx').on(table.taskId),
  index('notifications_scheduled_at_idx').on(table.scheduledAt),
  index('notifications_cascade_id_idx').on(table.cascadeId),
  index('notifications_type_idx').on(table.type),
]);
```

DRIZZLE SCHEMA - DELIVERY ATTEMPTS TABLE (one row per channel attempt):

```typescript
export const deliveryAttempts = pgTable('delivery_attempts', {
  id: uuid('id').primaryKey().defaultRandom(),
  notificationId: uuid('notification_id').references(() => notifications.id, { onDelete: 'cascade' }).notNull(),
  
  // Channel & Provider
  channel: notificationChannelEnum('channel').notNull(),
  provider: text('provider').notNull(),       // 'fcm', 'telegram_bot_api', 'gupshup', 'sendgrid', 'msg91'
  
  // Status tracking
  status: notificationStatusEnum('status').default('created').notNull(),
  
  // Timing
  queuedAt: timestamp('queued_at', { withTimezone: true }),
  processingAt: timestamp('processing_at', { withTimezone: true }),
  sentAt: timestamp('sent_at', { withTimezone: true }),
  deliveredAt: timestamp('delivered_at', { withTimezone: true }),
  readAt: timestamp('read_at', { withTimezone: true }),
  actedAt: timestamp('acted_at', { withTimezone: true }),
  failedAt: timestamp('failed_at', { withTimezone: true }),
  
  // Delivery details
  providerMessageId: text('provider_message_id'),  // ID from provider (for webhook matching)
  deliveryLatencyMs: integer('delivery_latency_ms'),
  
  // Retry tracking
  attemptNumber: integer('attempt_number').default(1).notNull(),
  maxAttempts: integer('max_attempts').notNull(),
  nextRetryAt: timestamp('next_retry_at', { withTimezone: true }),
  
  // Error details
  errorType: text('error_type'),              // NotificationErrorType
  errorMessage: text('error_message'),
  errorCode: text('error_code'),              // Provider-specific error code
  
  // Action tracking
  userAction: text('user_action'),            // 'mark_done', 'snooze', 'dismiss', null
  userActionAt: timestamp('user_action_at', { withTimezone: true }),
  
  // Cost
  costAmount: integer('cost_amount'),         // In paise (1/100 INR) for precision
  costCurrency: text('cost_currency').default('INR'),
  
  // BullMQ job reference
  bullmqJobId: text('bullmq_job_id'),
  
  createdAt: timestamp('created_at', { withTimezone: true }).defaultNow().notNull(),
  updatedAt: timestamp('updated_at', { withTimezone: true }).defaultNow().notNull(),
}, (table) => [
  index('delivery_attempts_notification_id_idx').on(table.notificationId),
  index('delivery_attempts_channel_idx').on(table.channel),
  index('delivery_attempts_status_idx').on(table.status),
  index('delivery_attempts_provider_message_id_idx').on(table.providerMessageId),
  index('delivery_attempts_created_at_idx').on(table.createdAt),
  // Composite for delivery rate calculations
  index('delivery_attempts_channel_status_idx').on(table.channel, table.status),
]);
```

DRIZZLE SCHEMA - USER CHANNEL PREFERENCES:

