ALERT RULES (Prometheus Alertmanager):

```yaml
groups:
  - name: notification_alerts
    rules:
      # Critical: Channel delivery rate dropped significantly
      - alert: NotificationDeliveryRateLow
        expr: |
          (
            sum(rate(unjynx_notifications_sent_total{status="success"}[15m])) by (channel)
            /
            sum(rate(unjynx_notifications_sent_total[15m])) by (channel)
          ) < 0.90
        for: 15m
        labels:
          severity: critical
        annotations:
          summary: "{{ $labels.channel }} delivery rate below 90%"
          description: "Channel {{ $labels.channel }} has a delivery rate of {{ $value | humanizePercentage }} over the last 15 minutes."

      # Warning: Queue depth growing
      - alert: NotificationQueueBacklog
        expr: unjynx_notification_queue_depth{state="waiting"} > 1000
        for: 10m
        labels:
          severity: warning
        annotations:
          summary: "{{ $labels.channel }} queue has {{ $value }} waiting jobs"

      # Critical: Dead letter queue growing
      - alert: DeadLetterQueueGrowing
        expr: rate(unjynx_notifications_dead_letter_total[30m]) > 0.1
        for: 10m
        labels:
          severity: critical
        annotations:
          summary: "Dead letter queue receiving {{ $value }}/s notifications"

      # Warning: Daily cost exceeding budget
      - alert: NotificationCostHigh
        expr: unjynx_notification_daily_cost_paise > 50000  # INR 500/day
        labels:
          severity: warning
        annotations:
          summary: "Daily notification cost has reached INR {{ $value | humanize }} paise"

      # Critical: Channel completely down
      - alert: NotificationChannelDown
        expr: unjynx_channel_health == 0
        for: 5m
        labels:
          severity: critical
        annotations:
          summary: "{{ $labels.channel }} channel is DOWN"

      # Warning: High cascade rate (primary channels failing often)
      - alert: HighCascadeRate
        expr: |
          rate(unjynx_notifications_cascaded_total[1h]) 
          / 
          rate(unjynx_notifications_sent_total[1h]) > 0.15
        for: 30m
        labels:
          severity: warning
        annotations:
          summary: "{{ $value | humanizePercentage }} of notifications are cascading to fallback channels"

      # Info: Cost projection exceeds monthly budget
      - alert: MonthlyCostProjectionHigh
        expr: |
          predict_linear(unjynx_notification_cost_paise_total[7d], 30*86400) > 1500000  # INR 15K/month
        labels:
          severity: info
        annotations:
          summary: "Projected monthly notification cost: INR {{ $value | humanize }} paise"
```

### 3.10 CHANNEL-SPECIFIC FAILURE MODES

PUSH (FCM):
- InvalidRegistration: Token expired -> remove token, disable push for user, cascade
- NotRegistered: App uninstalled -> same as above
- MessageTooBig: Payload > 4KB -> truncate and retry
- MismatchSenderId: Config error -> alert, cascade
- DeviceMessageRateExceeded: Too many to one device -> backoff, cascade
- TopicsMessageRateExceeded: Topic limit hit -> backoff

TELEGRAM:
- 403 Forbidden: User blocked bot -> disable telegram for user, cascade
- 429 Too Many Requests: Rate limit -> honor retry_after header
- 400 Bad Request: Invalid chat_id -> verify, disable, cascade
- 502 Bad Gateway: Telegram servers down -> retry with long backoff

WHATSAPP (Gupshup):
- Template not approved: -> cascade immediately, alert content team
- 24h window expired: -> cascade to non-windowed channel
- Rate limit (80 TPS): -> queue backpressure, honor retry-after
- Invalid phone number: -> disable whatsapp for user, cascade
- Insufficient balance: -> CRITICAL alert, cascade to free channels

EMAIL (SendGrid):
- Bounce (hard): -> disable email for user, cascade
- Bounce (soft): -> retry up to 3x, then cascade
- Spam complaint: -> disable email for user, alert, cascade
- Rate limit: -> backoff, retry
- Invalid email: -> disable, cascade

SMS (MSG91/Kaleyra):
- DND filtered: -> cascade (common in India, 10-15% of numbers)
- Invalid number: -> disable SMS for user, cascade
- Insufficient credits: -> CRITICAL alert, cascade to free channels
- Rate limit: -> backoff, retry
- Network unreachable: -> retry with exponential backoff

### 3.11 QUIET HOURS AND SCHEDULING

```typescript
const shouldSendNow = (
  userId: string,
  channel: NotificationChannel,
  channelPrefs: UserChannelPreference,
  notification: Notification,
): { send: boolean; delayMs?: number } => {
  // System notifications bypass quiet hours
  if (notification.type === 'system') {
    return { send: true };
  }
  
  // Urgent tasks bypass quiet hours
  if (notification.priority <= 2) {
    return { send: true };
  }
  
  // Check quiet hours
  if (channelPrefs.quietHoursEnabled) {
    const userNow = getCurrentTimeInUserTimezone(userId);
    const start = parseTime(channelPrefs.quietHoursStart!);  // e.g., 22:00
    const end = parseTime(channelPrefs.quietHoursEnd!);       // e.g., 07:00
    
    if (isInTimeRange(userNow, start, end)) {
      const delayMs = getMillisecondsUntil(end, userId);
      return { send: false, delayMs };
    }
  }
  
  return { send: true };
};
```

### 3.12 NOTIFICATION ORCHESTRATOR (Main Entry Point)

```typescript
const sendNotification = async (request: NotificationRequest): Promise<string> => {
  // 1. Validate input
  validateNotificationRequest(request);
  
  // 2. Resolve user preferences and cascade order
  const userPrefs = await getUserChannelPreferences(request.userId);
  const enabledChannels = userPrefs
    .filter(p => p.isEnabled && p.isConnected && !p.autoDisabledAt)
    .sort((a, b) => a.cascadePriority - b.cascadePriority);
  
  if (enabledChannels.length === 0) {
    // No channels available - store as in-app only
    return await createInAppNotification(request);
  }
  
  // 3. Create notification record
  const cascadeId = generateUUID();
  const notification = await createNotification({
    ...request,
    cascadeId,
    cascadeOrder: 0,
  });
  
  // 4. Always create in-app notification (stored, no queue needed)
  await createInAppNotification(request);
  
  // 5. Start cascade with first enabled channel
  const primaryChannel = enabledChannels[0];
  
  // 6. Check rate limits
  const rateCheck = await checkRateLimit(
    request.userId,
    primaryChannel.channel,
    primaryChannel.maxDailyMessages,
  );
  
  if (!rateCheck.allowed) {
    // Try next channel in cascade
    if (enabledChannels.length > 1) {
      return await startCascadeAtChannel(notification, enabledChannels, 1);
    }
    return notification.id; // Only in-app delivered
  }
  
  // 7. Check quiet hours
  const sendCheck = shouldSendNow(
    request.userId,
    primaryChannel.channel,
    primaryChannel,
    notification,
  );
  
  // 8. Create delivery attempt record
  const attempt = await createDeliveryAttempt({
    notificationId: notification.id,
    channel: primaryChannel.channel,
    provider: getProviderForChannel(primaryChannel.channel),
    status: 'queued',
    queuedAt: new Date(),
    maxAttempts: QUEUE_CONFIG[`notification:${primaryChannel.channel}`].attempts,
  });
  
  // 9. Add to channel queue
  const jobData: NotificationJobData = {
    notificationId: notification.id,
    deliveryAttemptId: attempt.id,
    userId: request.userId,
    channel: primaryChannel.channel,
    title: request.title,
    body: request.body,
    actionUrl: request.actionUrl,
    channelPayload: await buildChannelPayload(primaryChannel, request),
    cascadeId,
    cascadeOrder: 0,
    notificationType: request.type,
    priority: request.priority ?? JOB_PRIORITIES.NORMAL,
    taskId: request.taskId,
    contentId: request.contentId,
  };
  
  const queue = notificationQueues[primaryChannel.channel];
  await queue.add(`notify:${primaryChannel.channel}`, jobData, {
    priority: request.priority ?? JOB_PRIORITIES.NORMAL,
    delay: sendCheck.delayMs ?? 0,
    jobId: `${notification.id}:${primaryChannel.channel}:${attempt.attemptNumber}`,
  });
  
  // 10. Emit metrics
  notificationsSentCounter.inc({
    channel: primaryChannel.channel,
    status: 'queued',
    notification_type: request.type,
  });
  
  return notification.id;
};
```

### 3.13 IMPLEMENTATION PRIORITY

Phase 2 (Weeks 5-6): Foundation
- BullMQ queue setup (push + telegram only, both free)
- Basic notification orchestrator (no cascade yet)
- Delivery attempt tracking table
- Push notification worker (FCM)
- Telegram bot worker
- In-app notification storage

Phase 2 (Weeks 7-8): Cascade & Paid Channels
- WhatsApp worker (Gupshup integration)
- Email worker (SendGrid)
- Cascade engine (push -> telegram -> email)
- Rate limiting (per-user per-channel)
- Quiet hours support
- Delivery webhooks (WhatsApp status, Telegram callback)

Phase 3 (Weeks 9-10): SMS & Intelligence
- SMS worker (MSG91)
- Full cascade with all 5 channels
- Dead letter queue with admin UI
- Cost tracking and budget alerts
- User-configurable cascade order
- Auto-disable failing channels

Phase 4 (Weeks 11-12): Monitoring & Optimization
- Prometheus metrics for all channels
- Grafana notification dashboard
- Alert rules (all tiers)
- Cost optimization (prefer free channels)
- Delivery rate SLA monitoring
- Channel health scoring

